(Corrects typographical error in acronym in headline.)  The Securities Investor Protection
Corp. was ordered by a U.S judge in  Washington  to explain why it
shouldn’t create a claims process for R. Allen Stanford’s
alleged investment fraud victims.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Schoenberg in Washington at 
